@startuml "Checkout - Insufficient Stock"

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam shadowing false

title Checkout — Insufficient Stock

actor Client
participant "Nginx\nGateway" as GW
participant "Order Service\n(+ Saga Orchestrator)" as Order
database "order-db\n(+ tx log)" as OrderDB
queue "stock-commands\n(stream)" as SCS
participant "Stock\nService" as Stock
database "stock-db" as StockDB
queue "tx-responses\n(stream)" as SRS

== 1. Initiate Checkout ==
Client -> GW : POST /orders/checkout/{order_id}
GW -> Order : POST /checkout/{order_id}
Order -> OrderDB : read order\n(items, user_id, total_cost)
Order -> OrderDB : CREATE tx:{tx_id}\nstate=STARTED

== 2. Reserve Stock — FAILS ==
Order -> OrderDB : tx:{tx_id} state=RESERVING_STOCK
Order -> SCS : XADD stock-commands\n{tx_id, cmd=RESERVE_STOCK, items}
SCS -> Stock : XREADGROUP stock-commands
Stock -> StockDB : check stock
note right of Stock #Salmon : Insufficient stock!\nItem X has 2, need 5
Stock -> SRS : XADD tx-responses\n{tx_id, step=RESERVE_STOCK, status=FAILURE,\n reason="insufficient stock for item X"}
SRS -> Order : XREADGROUP tx-responses

== 3. No Compensation Needed ==
note right of Order #LightYellow : No prior steps succeeded,\nno compensation required.\nStock reservation was atomic\n(all-or-nothing).

== 4. Saga Aborted ==
Order -> OrderDB : tx:{tx_id} state=ABORTED
note right of Order #Salmon : Transaction aborted:\ninsufficient stock

Order --> GW : 400 Out of stock
GW --> Client : 400 Out of stock

@enduml
